Using redirect parameters after login is extremely dangerous without proper validation. This is called an Open Redirect vulnerability and it's commonly exploited in phishing attacks because the initial URL appears legitimate to users.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// login.php - VULNERABLE: Open redirect after authentication
session_start();

class AuthController {
    private $pdo;

    public function __construct($pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    public function login() {
        if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST') {
            $username = $_POST['username'] ?? '';
            $password = $_POST['password'] ?? '';

            // Authenticate user (simplified)
            $stmt = $this->pdo->prepare("SELECT id, password_hash FROM users WHERE username = ?");
            $stmt->execute([$username]);
            $user = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

            if ($user && password_verify($password, $user['password_hash'])) {
                $_SESSION['user_id'] = $user['id'];
                $_SESSION['logged_in'] = true;

                // VULNERABLE: Direct redirect without validation
                $redirect_url = $_GET['redirect'] ?? $_POST['redirect'] ?? '/dashboard';
                header("Location: " . $redirect_url);
                exit();
            }
        }

        // Display login form with hidden redirect field
        $redirect = htmlspecialchars($_GET['redirect'] ?? '/dashboard');
        echo '<form method="POST">';
        echo '<input type="hidden" name="redirect" value="' . $redirect . '">';
        echo '<input name="username" placeholder="Username">';
        echo '<input type="password" name="password" placeholder="Password">';
        echo '<button type="submit">Login</button>';
        echo '</form>';
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```text
https://legitimate-site.com/login.php?redirect=https://evil-phishing-site.com/fake-dashboard
https://legitimate-site.com/login.php?redirect=//evil-site.com
https://legitimate-site.com/login.php?redirect=https://legitimate-site.com.evil.com
https://legitimate-site.com/login.php?redirect=javascript:alert(document.cookie)
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- User sees legitimate login URL and trusts the site
- After successful authentication, user is redirected to attacker's phishing page
- Phishing page can mimic a "session expired" message to harvest credentials again
- Can be used to steal session tokens via crafted URLs
- Bypasses browser security indicators since initial domain is trusted

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
// login.php - SECURE: Validated redirect with whitelist
session_start();

class SecureAuthController {
    private $pdo;

    // Whitelist of allowed redirect paths (relative only)
    private $allowed_redirects = [
        '/dashboard',
        '/profile',
        '/settings',
        '/orders',
        '/account'
    ];

    public function __construct($pdo) {
        $this->pdo = $pdo;
    }

    /**
     * Validate redirect URL - only allow relative paths to same origin
     */
    private function validateRedirectUrl($url) {
        // Default safe redirect
        $default = '/dashboard';

        if (empty($url)) {
            return $default;
        }

        // Block any URL with protocol or domain indicators
        $dangerous_patterns = [
            '/^https?:\/\//i',      // http:// or https://
            '/^\/\//i',              // Protocol-relative //
            '/^javascript:/i',       // JavaScript pseudo-protocol
            '/^data:/i',             // Data URI
            '/^vbscript:/i',         // VBScript
            '/[\x00-\x1f]/i',        // Control characters
            '/@/',                    // URL with credentials
        ];

        foreach ($dangerous_patterns as $pattern) {
            if (preg_match($pattern, $url)) {
                error_log("Blocked malicious redirect attempt: " . substr($url, 0, 100));
                return $default;
            }
        }

        // Parse the URL and ensure it's a valid relative path
        $parsed = parse_url($url);

        // If it has a host component, it's absolute - reject
        if (isset($parsed['host'])) {
            return $default;
        }

        // Extract just the path component
        $path = $parsed['path'] ?? $default;

        // Ensure path starts with /
        if ($path[0] !== '/') {
            return $default;
        }

        // Normalize path to prevent directory traversal
        $path = '/' . ltrim($path, '/');

        // Check against whitelist (match path prefix)
        foreach ($this->allowed_redirects as $allowed) {
            if (strpos($path, $allowed) === 0) {
                return $path;
            }
        }

        return $default;
    }

    public function login() {
